## Payload storage

Qdrant supports two types of payload storages: InMemory and OnDisk.

InMemory payload storage is organized in the same way as in-memory vectors. The payload data is loaded into RAM at service startup while disk and [Gridstore](https://qdrant.tech/articles/gridstore-key-value-storage/) are used for persistence only. This type of storage works quite fast, but it may require a lot of space to keep all the data in RAM, especially if the payload has large values attached - abstracts of text or even images.
